<br>
 I was under the impression it worked exactly the same ad rogue Duelist discipline. And if you play a rogue or even just know them well you know it doubles their max backstab. Max normal BS with a 15dmg weapon and no mod is 553 I believe. And max Duelist in that situation is 1106. Max duelist crit in situation is 1888. <br>
<br>
1888/1106 = 1.71(roughly) <br>
<br>
 So for rogues crits seem to be 1.71x damage. Will use that number.<br>
<br>
 NOW here's what's throwing me off. Multiple warriors have gotten 1802 as max crip with TSBS + Fell Strike. So unless it does something odd to the crit/crip modifier the number should be higher. Somewhere around 2k damage.<br>
<br>
341(max normal) x 1.71 = 583 <br>
So 583 should be max CRIT. I think it's more like 591 though, not sure. Will stick with 583 to be safe.<br>
<br>
583 x 1.71 = 996<br>
996 should be max crip with no discs then, assuming Crips use the same formula as crits.<br>
<br>
996 x 2 = 1992<br>
190 points higher than the max crip actually is.<br>
<br>
 So somewhere in there I am wrong. I assume it's in how crips are calculated.<br>
